main event: A bright circular object was observed rising in the sky near Cannon AFB, New Mexico for two hours on March 22, 1966.
interesting points: The object changed color from orange to blue-white during the observation.,The observer noted that the object appeared to move toward them during the sighting.,The sighting began in darkness and continued until sunrise.,At sunrise, the object slowly diminished in brightness.,The conclusion of the investigation was that the object was Venus.
witness description: Stanley J. Lupinske, III, A1C, an air traffic controller at Cannon AFB, considered completely reliable by supervisor.
